Mpumalanga remains the province, with no coronavirus deaths. However, residents are still being encouraged to practice hygiene, and social distancing. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Mpumalanga remains the province with no coronavirus deaths. Residents are still being encouraged to practice hygiene and social distancing. But for a family of 32 in Msogwaba, Mpumalanga, it’s a totally different story. READ: Grieving in the time of COVID-19 Social distancing has been a huge challenge for them. The Mokoena family says complying with the lockdown regulations has been tough. There are 26 children and six adults living in the house. READ: Mpumalanga schools not ready to open: Sadtu One of the children, a 15-year-old boy, has brain cancer. The family says they are worried about his health, especially now with the coronavirus pandemic. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.